        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1498863819" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11992409627284719364">Like so, so many others, I saw the TED talk as it swept through popular culture (later with the help of Beyoncé), and for that reason I didn&apos;t mark this volume very high on my to-be-read pile. However, after receiving it as a just-because gift, I found it served me well one morning while waiting for the train.<br/><br/>I was happy to read that, though only slightly, she had expanded on some ideas for the print version of her talk. This is an absolutely fine introduction to feminism. She articulates import</span>
  <span id="freeText11992409627284719364" style="display:none">Like so, so many others, I saw the TED talk as it swept through popular culture (later with the help of Beyoncé), and for that reason I didn't mark this volume very high on my to-be-read pile. However, after receiving it as a just-because gift, I found it served me well one morning while waiting for the train.<br /><br />I was happy to read that, though only slightly, she had expanded on some ideas for the print version of her talk. This is an absolutely fine introduction to feminism. She articulates important ideas. However, it is not particularly groundbreaking, and I would have loved for this volume to have been expanded more to allow for a deeper exploration of the ideas she presents. At any rate, I am delighted with how passionately this book, the lecture and its ideas, have been taken up.</span>
