<div id="review_3737118591" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3737118591" />
    <a title="Ruxandra (4fără15)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15"><img alt="Ruxandra (4fără15)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594010864p2/54171221.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3737118591?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ruxandra (4fără15)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ruxandra (4fără15)" href="/user/show/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15">Ruxandra (4fără15)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/24734225-we-should-all-be-feminists">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15?shelf=read-in-2021">read-in-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15?shelf=21st-century">21st-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15?shelf=essay">essay</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15?shelf=ebook-read">ebook-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54171221-ruxandra-4f-r-15?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3737118591" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1649131065598537193">yes, everyone should read it – especially those “indifferent to” gender issues. I absolutely knew I’d enjoy this, and I agree with everything in here, but I feel like some of the points she made were incomplete (obviously, for the sake of conciseness). <br/><br/><i>Feminism is, of course, part of human rights in general – but to choose to use the vague expression </i>human rights<i> is to deny the specific and particular problem of gender. It would be a way of pretending that is was not women who have, for centurie</i></span>
  <span id="freeText1649131065598537193" style="display:none">yes, everyone should read it – especially those “indifferent to” gender issues. I absolutely knew I’d enjoy this, and I agree with everything in here, but I feel like some of the points she made were incomplete (obviously, for the sake of conciseness). <br /><br /><i>Feminism is, of course, part of human rights in general – but to choose to use the vague expression </i>human rights<i> is to deny the specific and particular problem of gender. It would be a way of pretending that is was not women who have, for centuries, been excluded. It would be a way of denying that the problem was not about being human, but specifically about being a female human. For centuries, the world divided human beings into two groups and then proceeded to exclude and oppress one group. It is only fair that the solution to the problem should acknowledge that.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="1649131065598537193" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


